title: High school volleyball: Fab fives
text:
Four victories away from a perfect 16-0 run in District 14-6A. 
2. Westwood (33-8) 
At 9-1, shares District 13-6A lead with Round Rock. 
3. Round Rock (30-10) 
Knocked Rouse out of share of first place in 13-6A. 
4. Lake Travis (22-12) 
Faces rival Westlake next week in a district clash. 
5. Rouse (28-15) 
Raiders get another crack at Westwood on Tuesday. 
• Class 5A 
Perfect 10-0 in District 25-5A after topping Cedar Park. 
2. Bastrop (27-11) 
At 14-0 in 26-5A, Bears have clinched first district title in volleyball. 
3. Vandegrift (33-8) 
Two of next three matches come against Cedar Park, Dripping Springs. 
4. Cedar Park (23-13) 
Slipped to 7-3 in District 25-5A after four-set loss to Tigers. 
5. Ann Richards (25-12) 
On Tuesday, has chance to end Bastrop’s unbeaten run in 26-5A. 
• Class 4A and below 
1. St. Michael’s (26-6) 
Crusaders lead their TAPPS district with a 6-0 record. 
2. La Grange (32-6) 
Sweep of Caldwell earns Leopards a share of first in 21-4A. 
3. Brentwood Christian (25-10) 
Bears sweep Round Rock Christian, lock up third straight district title. 
4. Thrall (29-7) 
Tigerettes have clinched a playoff berth from District 16-2A. 
5. Lago Vista (18-4) 
Vikings have won 27 of 31 sets while going unbeaten in 25-3A. 
Dig, set, spike 
Dripping Springs, the top-ranked team in the state in Class 5A, lost its first set in District 25-5A play on Tuesday, when the Tigers beat Cedar Park 25-23, 25-17, 22-25, 25-17. Tigers outside hitter Morgyn Greer , a University of Florida recruit, recorded 18 kills in the victory. … Senior outside hitter Courtney Markes piled up 20 kills and 14 digs Tuesday as Westwood defeated Hendrickson in four sets. The Warriors remain tied with Round Rock for the District 13-6A lead, with the teams scheduled to play at Round Rock on Oct. 27. … Hutto swept Waco University to improve to 9-0 in District 17-5A. The Hippos will face Temple on Friday. … Liberty Hill, Burnet and Salado are locked in a three-way tie for first place in District 25-4A. All three teams are 5-1 in district matches. … La Grange swept Caldwell 25-19, 25-17, 25-14 to avenge its lone loss in District 21-4A and forge a first-place tie in the league standings. … Avery Poppinga notched 16 kills as St. Stephen’s swept Houston Christian to improve to 3-0 in the Southwest Preparatory Conference. … Hyde Park (24-14) has only two losses in district play, both coming against St. Michael’s. 
Matches to watch 
Vandegrift at Cedar Park, 6:30 p.m. 
• Tuesday 
Bastrop at Ann Richards, 6:30 p.m. 
Rouse at Westwood, 6:30 p.m. 
Salado at Liberty Hill, 6:30 p.m. 
— Butch Hart, AA-S correspondent
